OL,7,FMr Wright said: "Flames broke through
OL,8,Fthe translucent roof exposing the
OL,9,Flibrary below to the elements.
OL,11,F"Smoke, water, glass, burned matter
OL,12,Ffrom the fire and damage from exposure
OL,13,Fto the elements have rendered the
OL,14,Flibrary and its 25,000 books an
OL,15,Finsurance write-off."
OL,17,FHe added the library has been put out
OL,18,Fof action until September 2025, 11
OL,19,Fclassrooms were periodically unusable,
OL,20,Fand "significant amounts" of science
OL,21,Fequipment were damaged irreparably.
