OL,3,CTeenager given referral order after
OL,4,Cstarting a fire at London Oratory
OL,5,CSchool
OL,7,FDuring a judgment hearing last month,
OL,8,Fdistrict judge Andrew Sweet ruled the
OL,9,Fendangering life charge should be
OL,10,Fdismissed as he believed the defendant
OL,11,F"did consider his actions" and "was
OL,12,Fintending to try and harm himself
OL,13,Frather than anyone else".
OL,15,FThe teenager wrote a note of apology
OL,16,Fand made a 999 call immediately after
OL,17,Fthe fire, but also kicked a responding
OL,18,Fpolice constable, the court heard
OL,19,Fpreviously.
